    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-09T10:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-09T10:30:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dwyre</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-09T12:00:00-03:30"
                            >July 9, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Referring to my telegram No. 49, July 6. In an extended conversation with the
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs yesterday he stated that he had given most careful
                    consideration to the contents of my informal memorandum and at this time could
                    only repeat what he has often declared publicly which he said was substantially
                    the following declaration of Uruguay’s foreign policy.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Uruguay is and has always been in favor of the closest possible cooperation
                        among the nations of the American continent and has reiterated that policy
                        on every occasion including the Pan American Conferences.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Full report by air mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dwyre</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
